@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "LGH Body Treatments ";
}

<div class="content contentmobilhome">
    @await Html.PartialAsync("_HeaderTratamientosFacial")

    <div class="mainmainbox">
        <div class="mainbox">
            <div class="textbodysecondtext">
                <h4>Facial Radiofrequency -</h4>
                <h5>Firm and Rejuvenate Without Surgery</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="imgcavitspain">
                <div class="mainboxradfacial">
                    <img src="~/images/Radiocila.jpg" width="50px" height="30px" class="imgradiofacmainpic" alt="Facial Radiofrequency Device" />
                    <div class="boxradfacial">
                        <h6>What is facial radiofrequency?</h6>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    Facial radiofrequency (RF) is a non-invasive cosmetic treatment that uses controlled thermal energy to stimulate the natural production of collagen and elastin in the deeper layers of the skin. This results in firmer, smoother, and more youthful-looking skin—without needles or surgical procedures.
                    It's an excellent option for those looking to tighten sagging skin, reduce fine lines, or revitalize a dull and tired complexion.
                </p>
                <div class="mainboxradfacialdos">
                    <div class="boxradfacialdos">
                        <img src="~/images/radiofrecuencia-facial-contexto.jpg" width="50px" height="30px" class="facialcontexto" alt="Facial Radiofrequency in Context" />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <h6>What is facial radiofrequency used for?</h6>
                <p class="radiofrequenciatextcuatro">
                    Facial radiofrequency helps improve:<br />
                    ✅ Sagging skin on the face, jawline, and neck<br />
                    ✅ Fine lines and early wrinkles<br />
                    ✅ Dull or lackluster skin<br />
                    ✅ Bags and dark circles under the eyes<br />
                    ✅ Poor facial contour definition<br />
                    ✅ Enlarged pores and uneven skin texture<br />
                    It’s also an anti-aging preventative treatment, ideal for maintaining firm and healthy skin over time.<br />
                </p>
                <h6>Benefits of facial radiofrequency</h6>
                <p>
                    ✨ Naturally stimulates collagen production<br />
                    ✨ Quick, painless treatment with no downtime<br />
                    ✨ Warm and relaxing sensation, like a facial massage<br />
                    ✨ Improves skin texture and tone<br />
                    ✨ Visible results after just a few sessions<br />
                    ✨ Safe for nearly all skin types and tones<br />
                </p>
                <h6>What is the treatment like?</h6>
                <p>
                    Each session lasts between 30 and 45 minutes. A specialized device emits radiofrequency waves over the skin, generating heat in the dermis (the deepest layer) without damaging the surface. This heat stimulates cell regeneration and the production of new collagen.
                    Most patients describe the procedure as comfortable and pleasant, with no pain or discomfort. No recovery time is needed.
                </p>
                <h6>Recommended treatment plan</h6>
                <p>
                    ⚡ Number of sessions: 4 to 6 for optimal results<br />
                    ⚡ Frequency: Once a week or every 15 days<br />
                    ⚡ Maintenance: 1 session every 1–3 months to prolong the effects<br />
                    <button class="btn-theme-home btn-precios"><a asp-controller="Spanish" asp-action="Precios" class="btn-home-page">Check our prices</a></button>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

